#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:343
#, no-wrap
msgid "Partition setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:347
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"OK, now it's time to prepare some disk partitions, of which you'll \n"
"need at least two. If you're using RAID-0, make sure they're on \n"
"separate disks and approximately the same size. It goes without \n"
"saying that the data on these partitions will be destroyed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:354
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"One other important note -- when you create your partitions, give \n"
"them the partition type <c>FD</c>. This will allow the Linux \n"
"kernel to recognize them as Linux RAID partitions, so they will be \n"
"autodetected and started at every boot. If you don't mark your \n"
"RAID partitions this way, you'll need to type \n"
"<c>raidstart --all</c> after every boot before you can mount your \n"
"RAID volumes. That can be annoying, so set the partition type \n"
"correctly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:367
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/raidtab setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:371
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The raidtab syntax is fairly easy to figure out: each block of \n"
"directives begins with a <c>raiddev</c> entry specifying the RAID \n"
"volume that will be created. When you installed raidtools, the \n"
"Makefile created <path>/dev/md0</path> through <path>md15</path> \n"
"for you, so they're available for use.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:379
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next, <c>nr-raid-disks</c> should specify the number of disks in \n"
"your array. Then you set the <c>persistent-superblock</c> to \n"
"<c>1</c>, telling the raid tools that when this volume is \n"
"created, a special superblock should be written to each \n"
"constituent device describing the configuration of the RAID \n"
"array. The Linux kernel uses this information to auto-detect and \n"
"start up RAID arrays at boot time, so you should make sure that \n"
"every RAID volume you create is configured to do this.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:390
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<c>chunk-size</c> specifies the granularity of the chunks used \n"
"for RAID-0 in kilobytes. In this example, our RAID-0 volume will \n"
"write to its constituent partitions in 32K blocks; that is, the \n"
"first 32K of the RAID volume maps to <path>hde1</path>, the \n"
"second 32K maps to <path>hdg1</path>, etc. We also specify a \n"
"chunk size for our <path>/dev/md1</path> linear volume -- this is \n"
"just a dummy entry and doesn't mean anything.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:400
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Finally, you specify the devices that make up the volume. First \n"
"you specify the actual block device with a <c>device</c> line, \n"
"and then you immediately follow it with a <c>raid-disk</c> entry \n"
"that specifies its position in the array, starting with zero.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:407
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once you've created your own <path>/etc/raidtab</path> file, \n"
"you're ready to do a one-time initialization of the array.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:414
#, no-wrap
msgid "mkraid and creating the filesystem"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:418
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"OK. Our partitions are created, the raidtab file is in place -- \n"
"now it's time to initialize our first partition by using the \n"
"<c>mkraid</c> command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:423
#, no-wrap
msgid "Initializing the partition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:424
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>mkraid /dev/md0</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:428
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"After this command completes, <path>/dev/md0</path> will be \n"
"initialized and the md0 array will be started. If you type \n"
"<c>cat /proc/mdstat</c>, you should see something like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:433
#, no-wrap
msgid "cat /proc/mdstat"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/software-raid-p1.xml:434
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Personalities : [linear] [raid0] [raid1] [raid5]\n"
"read_ahead 1024 sectors\n"
"md0 : active raid0 hdg1[1] hde1[0]\n"
"      90069632 blocks 32k chunks\n"
" \n"
